{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad331719-ac3e-4058-ad89-627eae12de1c","content":"`.testsettings` is a legacy format dropped in MSTest v3. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your file configures and how each setting maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` (30 000 ms) | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code coverage data collector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | No longer needed — modern test platform handles this natively |\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` file and wire it up in the project.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JSLSRw14aepAvEgsY1Rgwm","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Uneu54fFjbEkaM8hYv3De5","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7fcd74286e994c80b4cb943af0efaa02/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Migrated from .testsettings TestTimeout property -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <!-- Migrated from .testsettings CodeCoverage data collector -->\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.CodeCoverage.IO.CodeCoverageDataCollector, Microsoft.CodeCoverage.IO\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-7fcd74286e994c80b4cb943af0efaa02/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01UBPMhe93DAVkEjcwZoVwfh","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7fcd74286e994c80b4cb943af0efaa02/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7fcd74286e994c80b4cb943af0efaa02/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a1a43518-9c16-429a-8378-49bf5834d289","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment configuration\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. A code coverage data collector\n\nMSTest v3 no longer supports `.testsettings` files. The configuration needs to be migrated to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest v3 attributes/properties.\n\nLet me provide the migration guidance:\n\n1. **Test timeout**: In MSTest v3, you can set a default timeout via `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` or use `[Timeout]` attributes.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector**: This goes into `.runsettings` under `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment**: MSTest v3 handles deployment differently. The `useLoadContext` setting is no longer needed as the modern test platform handles assembly loading natively.\n\nSince `.testsettings` is a legacy format and MSTest v3 uses `.runsettings` exclusively, I'll create the new `.runsettings` file and update the `.csproj` if needed.","outputTokens":954,"requestId":"0422:A737D:173A2C7:18A3A93:6A03376E"},"id":"57c04083-d22b-4f88-bcd9-74d4903ee8c4","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:48.547Z","parentId":"6c4f2f3d-af9e-4a48-aee7-5e25825ff01f"}
